t methodology enables systematic ab initio calculations of optical\nabsorption spectra at finite temperature, including both direct and indirect\ntransitions. This feature will be useful for high-throughput calculations of\noptical properties at finite temperature, and for calculating\ntemperature-dependent optical properties using high-level theories such as GW\nand Bethe-Salpeter approaches.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 8 Apr 2016 16:37:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 15 Jul 2016 18:23:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-17"}
