 the first-scale cells. The third-scale\ncellular structures are advected by the first-scale and second-scale convective\nflows. The spatial spectrum of the flow does not directly indicate the presence\nof the second-scale and third-scale structures; however, they can be selected\nby using our processing techniques. On the whole, the simulated flow pattern\nqualitatively resembles that observed on the Sun.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 9 Apr 2016 09:25:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 9 Jan 2018 12:52:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-15"}
